        "created_at": "2026-01-03T13:00:37.786Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I got this issue now for a second time.<br>\nSome time ago, I also had this bad behavior…</p>\n<p>You install some general Updates at your Linux-PC, and during Signal-Start you got an error like:</p>\n<pre data-code-wrap=\"bash\"><code class=\"lang-bash\">Database startup error:\n\nError: Error while decrypting the ciphertext provided to safeStorage.decryptString.at getSQLKey ([REDACTED]/app/main.main.js:1249:39)at initializeSQL ([REDACTED]/app/main.main.js:1341:11)at EventEmitter. ([REDACTED]/app/main.main.js:1589:20)\n\nApp Version: 7.83.0OS: linux\n</code></pre>\n<p>Ok, there is an easy way to re-init Signal, BUT this remove all Data which is older than 45 Days (if you are not in a payed plan).</p>\n<p>Don’t get me wrong with the following… I’ve donate multiple times to Signal in the past and I love the privacy that comes with it…<br>\nBut for me, it’s a no-go, that Media &gt; 45 Days wouldn’t be synchronized to the new connected Clients.<br>\nWhy is it so? Is there any way to restore / repair the old db to keep the history-stuff.<br>\nI really think about to switch to other messengers, because of this bad annoying behavior of Signal.</p>\n<p>Any Ideas or suggestion for Workarounds?</p>",
